Experiment 1 : setting up and basic commmands
Step1: git init //Inititalize new repository
step2: notepad filename.c - Save // Create New File
Step3: git add filename.c // Add to Staging Area
Step4: git commit -m "Your message" // Create Version

To Change Author : git commit --amend --author="New Author Name <New Email>"

Experiment 2 :creating and managing branches 1
Step1 : git branch "feature-Branch"
Step2 : git checkout "feature-Branch"
Step3 : Create File/Commit
Step4 : git checkout master
Step5 : git merge "feature-Branch"
Step6 : git log

Experiment 3:creating and managing branches 2
Step1 : notepad filename.txt
Step2 : git add filename.txt
Step3 : git commit -m "commit message here"
Step4 : repeat the Step1 - Update the file
Step5 : git add filename.txt
Step6 : git stash save "Your Stash message here"
Step7 : git status
Step8 : git branch "new-branch" / git checkout -b "branch-name"
Step9 : git checkout "new-branch"
Step10 : git stash apply
Step11: git status/log

Experiment 4 : collaboratuion and remote repositories 1
git init
- vi filename // create/update new file
- git add filename // add to staging area
- git commit -m "commit message here"
-> git clone <URL>

Exp 5:collaboratuion and remote repositories 2
git init
- vi filename // create/update new file
- git add filename // add to staging area
- git commit -m "commit message here"
- git remote add origin https://github.com/ngyatheesh/demo24.git
- git fetch origin/main
- git rebase origin/main
- git push -u origin main

Experiment 6:collaboratuion and remote repositories 3
- notepad filename //create file and add content
- git add filename // add to staging area
- git commit -m "commit message here"
- git branch "branch-name" // creating the branch
- git checkout "branch-name"
- notepad filename // edit previously created file
- git add filename
- git commit -m "commit message"
- git checkout master
- git merge "branch-name"
- git log/show/status

Experiment 7:git tags and release
- notepad filename //create file and add content
- git add filename // add to staging area
- git commit -m "commit message here"
- git tag "v1.0"
- OR git tag "v1.0" <commit ID>

Experiment 8:advanced git operations
- create and checkout new branch
- create file
- add and commit
- checkout to main branch
- git cherry-pick <commit ID>


Experiment 9:analysing and changing git history 1

- notepad filename // create and update the file
- git add filename // Add file to staging area
- git commit -m "commit message"
- git log --oneline
- git show <commit ID>
- git log -n 1 <commit ID>

Experiment 10:analysing and changing git history 2

- notepad filename // create and update the file
- git add filename // Add file to staging area
- git commit --author="JohnDoe <johndoe@gmail.com>" -m "commit message"
- git log --author="JohnDoe" --since="2025-01-01" --until="2025-12-31"

Experiment 11:analysing and changing git history 3
- notepad filename // create and update the file
- git add filename // Add file to staging area
- git commit -m "commit message"
- Repeat above 3 steps more than 5 times
- git log -n 5

Experiment 12:analysing and changing git history 4
- notepad filename // create and update the file
- git add filename // Add file to staging area
- git commit -m "commit message"
- Repeat above 3 steps
- git log --oneline
- git revert <commit ID>
